        {
            "date": "2009-09-30 10:04:52", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "If we can't import these, it's a bug.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Not being able to create them in the bookmarks section is Working As Intended.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I'm \nnot surprised people don't understand this -- the fraction of Firefox users who \nunderstand bookmark keywords is infinitesimal, and that functionality has been \naround a lot longer.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "\"Search engine\" is generally a better description of these than \"bookmark\" because (a) \nyou're substituting in some kind of query text to get a page that varies as a function \nof that text, and (b) it makes no sense to click on these directly since there's nothing \nto substitute in;", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "they're only useful from the address bar.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "/u/pkasting@chromium.org/", 
            "email": "/u/pkasting@chromium.org/"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2009-09-30 10:56:56", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "glad at least you recognize the inability to import them is a bug.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "its your service, so if you wanna hide some Keyworded URL Functionality under a 'Manage' button in the 'Default Search' \nsection of 'Options,' thats your choice, but understand that it is hiding it.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "keyworded url functionality has nothing to \ndo with setting your default search engine.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "period.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "if the suggestion to mimic firefox doesnt appeal to you, then maybe this will: both 'bookmarks' and 'default search' \nsections arent really the best place for keywords, and thus i suggest you break off from the firefox setup and create a new \narea in chrome options for keywords altogether.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "since the bookmarks section is probably where you will continue to store \nthese url settings i would argue its best to include any new keyword 'area' in the bookmark management section, but if not \nthats fine too.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "oh, and creating a new section might also have the effect of highlighting its existence to people who do \nlook around at their options, and maybe increase its userbase, not that it matters.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "[you still havent explained _why_ you \ndont allow creating them in bookmarks -- especially when firefox does -- unless your explanation is that the low fraction \nof users of something is a determinant to whether it is 'working as intended.'", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "]", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "either way, as i said, thanks for helping me figure out where i can use them, since this was the last major obstacle to \nconverting full time to chrome.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "now if only i didnt have to clear my cache (practically) once daily to keep my youtube \nmusic favorites list streaming in the background while i work (-;", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "/u/jamesp/", 
